The International DevelopmentAssociation said it approved a 114 mln dlr credit for India tosupport several water irrigation projects.    IDA, the World Bank arm which lends to the poorestcountries, said the projects are designed to increaseagricultural productivity and farm incomes.    Irrigation development has been a major factor in improvingagricultural performance and yields in many areas but fallshort of their potential due to unreliable water supply andoften inequitable distribution, it noted.    IDA said the credit supports a 7-year program to plan,implement and monitor improved operation of selected projects.    In addition to the 50-year credit, the Indian government andparticipating states will provide 43 mln dlrs to the plan. Reuter&#3;